#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:2
msgid "CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:6
msgid ""
"Specify a :ref:`semicolon-separated list <CMake Language Lists>` of parts "
"for the :command:`ctest_submit` command to submit in a :manual:`ctest(1)` :"
"ref:`Dashboard Client` script, or on the :program:`ctest` command line via "
"the :ctest-dashboard-option:`-D` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:12
msgid ""
"Valid part names are the same as those accepted by the ``PARTS`` option of :"
"command:`ctest_submit`: ``Start``, ``Update``, ``Configure``, ``Build``, "
"``Test``, ``Coverage``, ``MemCheck``, ``Submit``, ``Notes``, ``ExtraFiles``, "
"``Upload``, and ``Done``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:17
msgid ""
"If the :command:`ctest_submit` command is given an explicit ``PARTS`` "
"argument, that argument takes precedence and this variable is ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:20
msgid ""
"When this variable is empty or unset (and no explicit ``PARTS`` argument is "
"given), all available parts are submitted (the default behavior)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:23
msgid ""
"Example --- submit only the Configure result in a single ``ctest`` "
"invocation::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS.rst:25
msgid "ctest -T Configure -T Submit -D CTEST_SUBMIT_PARTS=Configure"
msgstr ""
